results.name: Relative class number h- of cyclotomic field Q(zeta_n).
comment: Note that if n == 2 (mod 4), Q(zeta_n) is the same field as Q(zeta_{n/2}).
For prime p, p divides a(p) (or a(2p)) if and only if p is in A000928.
For prime p, p divides a(4p) if and only if p is in A250216. (End)
link: Richard N. Smith, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..256 (terms 1..163 from R. J. Mathar)
L. C. Washington, Introduction to Cyclotomic Fields, Springer, p. 353. [WARNING: The table contains errors for n=59, 97, ...]
example: Q(zeta_23) = 3 is the first time that h- is bigger than 1.
xref: Contains A000927, A035115, A061494 as subsequences.
